Gregory Gaye https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gregory_Gaye 0 Gregory Gaye (October 10, 1900 – August 23, 1993) was a Russian-American character actor. The son of an actor, he was born Gregory de Gay in St. Petersburg, Russia. He was the uncle of actor George Gaynes. He was a cadet in the Imperial Russian Navy and began his stage career in Europe and in the Orient before going to the United States after the Russian Revolution in 1923. He appeared in small roles in over a hundred movies. Gregory_Gaye ( October_10_,_1900 – August_23_,_1993 ) was a_Russian-American_character_actor .
